                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.804,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 71931,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 02-1624, Elk Grove Unified School District versus Newdow will be announced by Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.804,
                        "stop": 355.727,
                        "byte_start": 71931,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.804,
                                "stop": 15.024,
                                "byte_start": 71931,
                                "byte_stop": 88858,
                                "text": "This case comes to us from the Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.024,
                                "stop": 25.942,
                                "byte_start": 88858,
                                "byte_stop": 132535,
                                "text": "Each day elementary school teachers in the Elk Grove Unified School District lead their classes in a group recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.942,
                                "stop": 32.766,
                                "byte_start": 132535,
                                "byte_stop": 159807,
                                "text": "Respondent, Michael A. Newdow, is an atheist whose daughter participates in that daily exercise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.766,
                                "stop": 44.634,
                                "byte_start": 159807,
                                "byte_stop": 207245,
                                "text": "The text of the pledge, as Congress amended it exactly 50 years ago today on Flag Day 1954, contains the words \u0022under God\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.634,
                                "stop": 53.981,
                                "byte_start": 207245,
                                "byte_stop": 244652,
                                "text": "For that reason, Newdow contends that the School District is engaged in unconstitutional religious indoctrination of his child."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.981,
                                "stop": 58.242,
                                "byte_start": 244652,
                                "byte_stop": 261684,
                                "text": "A divided panel of the Court of Appeals agreed with Newdow."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.242,
                                "stop": 74.493,
                                "byte_start": 261684,
                                "byte_stop": 326677,
                                "text": "In light of the obvious importance of that decision, we granted the School District\u2019s petition for certiorari to review the First Amendment issue and preliminarily the question whether Newdow has standing to invoke the jurisdiction of the Federal Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.493,
                                "stop": 91.097,
                                "byte_start": 326677,
                                "byte_stop": 393132,
                                "text": "The very purpose of the National Flag is to serve as the symbol of our country and of its proud traditions, of freedom, of equal opportunity, of religious tolerance, and of goodwill for other people who share our aspirations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.097,
                                "stop": 96.96,
                                "byte_start": 393132,
                                "byte_stop": 416538,
                                "text": "The Pledge of Allegiance evolved as a common public acknowledgment of those ideals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.96,
                                "stop": 113.83,
                                "byte_start": 416538,
                                "byte_stop": 484039,
                                "text": "Its recitation is a patriotic exercise that fosters national unity and also satisfies a California statutory requirement that every public school begin each day with an appropriate patriotic exercise."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.83,
                                "stop": 127.08,
                                "byte_start": 484039,
                                "byte_stop": 537015,
                                "text": "After the Court of Appeals issued its initial decision invalidating the District\u2019s pledge policy, Sandra Banning, the mother of Newdow\u0027s daughter, filed a motion for leave to intervene."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.08,
                                "stop": 149.362,
                                "byte_start": 537015,
                                "byte_stop": 626145,
                                "text": "She declared that although she and Newdow share physical custody of their daughter, a State Court order, and actually two or three order, granted her exclusive legal custody of the child including the sole right to represent the daughter\u2019s legal interest and make all decisions about her education and welfare."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.362,
                                "stop": 162.141,
                                "byte_start": 626145,
                                "byte_stop": 677240,
                                "text": "Banning further stated that her daughter is a Christian who believes in God and has no objection to reciting the pledge or to hear others recite it or to its reference to God."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.141,
                                "stop": 169.583,
                                "byte_start": 677240,
                                "byte_stop": 707020,
                                "text": "Banning expressed the belief that her daughter would be harmed if the litigation were permitted to proceed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.583,
                                "stop": 192.79,
                                "byte_start": 707020,
                                "byte_stop": 799911,
                                "text": "In response to Banning\u0027s motion, the Court of Appeals held that they could no longer sue on the child\u2019s behalf as her best friend but that he did have standing to sue to vindicate his own personal interest, specifically his interest in inculcating his child with his views about religion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.79,
                                "stop": 201.751,
                                "byte_start": 799911,
                                "byte_stop": 835751,
                                "text": "Our standing requirement enforces both constitutional and prudential limits on the powers of the unelected members of the federal judiciary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 201.751,
                                "stop": 221.414,
                                "byte_start": 835751,
                                "byte_stop": 914432,
                                "text": "Our standing jurisprudence contains two strands: the jurisdictional article three standing which enforces the constitution\u2019s case or controversy requirement, and prudential standing which embodies judicially self-imposed limits on the exercise of federal jurisdiction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 221.414,
                                "stop": 229.555,
                                "byte_start": 914432,
                                "byte_stop": 946928,
                                "text": "One of the principal areas in which this Court has exercised judicial restraint is in the realm of domestic relations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.555,
                                "stop": 241.632,
                                "byte_start": 946928,
                                "byte_stop": 995203,
                                "text": "Long ago, we observed that the whole subject of the domestic relations of husband and wife, parent and child, belonged to the laws of the States and not to the laws of the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.632,
                                "stop": 270.062,
                                "byte_start": 995203,
                                "byte_stop": 1108992,
                                "text": "The case before us today concerns not merely Newdow\u0027s interest in educating his child and teaching her about religious matters, but also that sometimes conflicting interests of the child\u2019s mother and of greater importance, the interest of a young child who finds herself at the center of a highly public debate involving the differing views of her parents, the validity of a national ritual, and the meanign of our Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.062,
                                "stop": 280.186,
                                "byte_start": 1108992,
                                "byte_stop": 1149430,
                                "text": "The case is unique because Newdow\u0027s standing derives entirely from his relationship with his daughter but he lacks the right to litigate as her next friend."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 280.186,
                                "stop": 291.56,
                                "byte_start": 1149430,
                                "byte_stop": 1194987,
                                "text": "In marked contrast to our normal third party standing cases, the interest of this parent and this child, instead of being parallel, are potentially in conflict."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 291.56,
                                "stop": 307.214,
                                "byte_start": 1194987,
                                "byte_stop": 1257576,
                                "text": "For reasons stated at a greater length in an opinion filed with the Clerk, we conclude that having been deprived under California law of the right to sue as his daughter\u2019s next friend, Newdow lacks prudential standing to bring this suit in Federal Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 307.214,
                                "stop": 311.491,
                                "byte_start": 1257576,
                                "byte_stop": 1274713,
                                "text": "Accordingly, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 311.491,
                                "stop": 326.155,
                                "byte_start": 1274713,
                                "byte_stop": 1333332,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in which Justice O\u2019Connor has joined and in which Justice Thomas has joined as to part 1; Justice O\u2019Connor and Justice Thomas also have filed opinions concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 326.155,
                                "stop": 334.594,
                                "byte_start": 1333332,
                                "byte_stop": 1367082,
                                "text": "Each of the three concurring opinions concludes that Newdow does have standing and that the pledge policy is constitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 334.594,
                                "stop": 355.727,
                                "byte_start": 1367082,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia took no part in the consideration or decision of the case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
